
<Lesson stage="2" page="7" type="Reading Check">
<APageParagraph activityIntroClip="uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3"  pencil="p3" skipIntro="true">
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Every year many people go hiking.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Their dream is to live a simple life off the beaten path for a short time.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>For some backpackers, the complete lack of cars and trucks on the trails suits them best.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Each part of the country has many different trails.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Some trails are short and take only a day to walk.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		  <text>These trails might be near your home.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		  <text>You could take bread, cold cuts and drinks for a picnic.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
    </sentence>      
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>It's great to get the feeling of open spaces and blue skies.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Not having to carry a heavy pack which weighs a ton is good too.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
		  <text>Or you could pick one of the other trails which are tougher.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>You can walk at a great height up into the mountains.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>Or you could wind your way down to sea level over a week or so.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>The oldest of these longer backpacking trails begins in Maine and ends in Georgia.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
     </sentence> 
	  </paragraph>
  <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The choice is yours, if you go for a short walk or a long hike.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Take a deep breath and head off.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		 <text>The fun thing is to have nothing in front of you but the open trail.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		 <text>When you have had enough you can go back to the city.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
    </sentence>
   </paragraph>
